==Demographics==

Hornitos first appeared as a census-designated place in the 2010 census. The Mariposa County Planning Department's 2010 census summary reported 75 residents, 43 housing units, 34 occupied housing units and nine vacant units in the CDP.<ref name="Census2010" />

At the 2020 census, Hornitos had 38 residents and 37 housing units, of which 24 were occupied and 13 were vacant; this represented a 49.3 percent population decline from 2010.<ref name="DOFProfile" /><ref name="Census2010" /> The California Department of Finance's redistricting profile, based on U.S. Census Bureau Public Law 94-171 data, reported a population density of 32.9 people per square mile. The Department of Finance's race tabulations exclude Hispanic respondents from each racial category and report Hispanic or Latino origin separately; raw Census Bureau P1 tabulations count Hispanic respondents within each race.<ref name="DOFProfile" /><ref name="Census2020P1" />

